// Doris in the background, holding bread (the Echo Web's source material).
Codex: A small framed photograph. Two figures. A bench. The image is faded.
Codex: One of them is younger Gerrold. The other — Margery, perhaps.
Codex: In the background, a woman with bread.

<<adjust_predecessor_trail 1>>

===

title: Codex_BedroomDoor_Cottage
tags: examine codex cottage bedroom_door m1_2_locked
---
// Mission 2 Guide § 13.1, § 25.3 — the closed bedroom door.
// Vow 7 silent bonus for the player who knows not to open it.
Codex: A closed bedroom door. The handle is brass.
Codex: It has been polished recently. The light underneath is steady.
Codex: You feel — clearly, suddenly — that you should not open this door today.
Codex: You believe Gerrold, also, has not opened it in some time.

<<adjust_vow "vow7" 1>>

===

title: Codex_Toolbox_Cottage
tags: examine codex cottage toolbox carpentry
---
// Mission 2 Guide § 13.1, § 25.4 — Gerrold's carpenter's tools.
// Mission 6+ seed: Gerrold will offer to make the player a wooden box.
Codex: A leather toolbox under Gerrold's chair.
Codex: Carpenter's chisels, a hammer, a block plane.
Codex: The blade of the plane is dull. He has not used these in some weeks.

===

title: Codex_ColdTeaCup
